CHECK:SPACING: No space is necessary after a cast
#41: FILE: drivers/char/tty_io.c:2012:
+		ltp = (struct ktermios *) kzalloc(sizeof(struct ktermios),

Whitespace style used in the kernel sources is described in kernel docs.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

WARNING:UNNECESSARY_CASTS: unnecessary cast may hide bugs, see http://c-faq.com/malloc/mallocnocast.html
#41: FILE: drivers/char/tty_io.c:2012:
+		ltp = (struct ktermios *) kzalloc(sizeof(struct ktermios),

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*ltp)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct ktermios)...)
#41: FILE: drivers/char/tty_io.c:2012:
+		ltp = (struct ktermios *) kzalloc(sizeof(struct ktermios),

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*driver)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct tty_driver)...)
#66: FILE: drivers/char/tty_io.c:3733:
+	driver = kzalloc(sizeof(struct tty_driver), GFP_KERNEL);

